    "industrial_process_notes": "Wallace Carothers' DuPont team first made nylon 6,6 on February 28, 1935 (publicly announced October 27, 1938, after Carothers' death); commercial nylon stockings launched in 1940. Equivalent amounts of hexamethylenediamine and adipic acid are combined in water; removing water drives amide-bond formation (polymerization). The resulting polymer can be extruded into granules or directly melt-spun into fiber. ~2 million tonnes produced worldwide as of 2011.",
